reviews.review_text: New Years '79 I almost wanted to give this 4 stars, because some of the solos burned like a yule log, hot. Not sure if they were well rested and fat from the Christmas break? No doubt they were getting revved up for an end of the decade, bay area NYE run. Lots of energy here, but the reason I only gave it 3 was it seems a bit disjointed as the notes explain. A few cut-outs etc. I liked the Me & My Uncle > River, the NFA, and the disco trippy Shakedown brought a smile. Otherwise, some high energy solos make it noteworthy.

I hope he got the sense to run.. picking it up with the Soundboard
Dire Wolf-even with lyric malfunctions-nice version
super tight Me & My Uncle>Big River
Brent is a blood transfusion in 79
B.E. Women- again even with lyric humming
this is a nice version,, good flow.
Minglewood-Snap Crackle Pop!
FOTD-mellow but perky tragedy tune
LLR-best slot late 1st set, go get em Weir!
Overall set is wild determined especially Alabama Getaway
- this is the Chuck Berry version. HEADY!
and comes with a Promised chaser.
 Set 2: calculate just how much ground they covered 
with that massive Uncle John's sandwich.
pre drums- UJB>Estimated (18 min with Caution riffing) 
>He's Gone>Other One (rarity into drums and fierce)
"Prospector your out of your box!" T-STORY
post drums- Great jam heavy Phil zone into N.F.A 
and Brokedown in the last ballad of the night slot
two from the Chuck Berry catalog to close the night
and it is slam dance city.
Shakedown in da funky encore slot.
just gotta poke around..
and a not even on the radar UJB reprise!
yeah a solid 5 star show.
